The order of the script is as follows: Opening - First prompt - Request for additional answers - Response to the first prompt - Second prompt - Request for additional answers - Response to the second prompt - Third prompt - Request for additional answers - Response to the third prompt - Fourth prompt - Request for additional answers - Response to the fourth prompt - Fifth prompt - Request for additional answers - Response to the fifth prompt - Closing remarks.

In the opening, explain the rules of the game to be played today and also explain how to participate. 

After giving the prompt, provide about 30 seconds of waiting music for listeners to answer. 

After 30 seconds, when requesting additional answers, include an encouraging remark to help listeners guess the correct answer, and add another 10 seconds of waiting music.

During the closing, encourage participation by discussing thoughts on today's broadcast and include a remark suggesting to play more fun games together next time.
